<CENTER><P><FONT COLOR="#708570"><FONT SIZE=+4>Welcome to VidaMed</FONT></FONT>
</P></CENTER>

<P><!-- Horizontal Line Tag -->
<HR></P>

<P>VidaMed designs, develops, manufactures and markets technologically
and clinically advanced, cost effective systems for the treatment of urological
conditions. </P>

<P>The Company's principal product, the <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.vidamed.com/tuna.html">TransUrethral
Needle Ablation</A>, or TUNA<SUP><FONT SIZE=+1>&reg;</FONT></SUP>, System
is a cost-effective, minimally-invasive alternative <!-- Link Tag -->for
the treatment of <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.vidamed.com/patient.html">symptoms
associated with benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH)</A> a noncancerous enlargement
of the prostate which restricts urine flow. The TUNA Procedure is performed
in an office or outpatient setting and does not require general anesthesia.</P>

<P>VidaMed received FDA clearance to market the TUNA System in the United
States on October 8, 1996. VIDAMED also markets the TUNA System <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.vidamed.com/distributor.html">in
over 20 countries throughout Europe and Asia.</A>, Founded in 1992, VidaMed
is headquartered in Menlo Park, California and publicly traded on the NASDAQ
market under the symbol <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.vidamed.com/investor.html">&quot;VIDA&quot;</A>.
</P>

